Robot Arm Demo
===============================================================================

The robot arm demo shows that host contexts are not limited to the browser.

The demo host exposes command and state contexts:

```text
robot://{instance}/commands
robot://{instance}/state
```

The command context supports `move`, `grip`, and `home`. The state context supports `read`.

1. Files
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```text
hosts/robot-arm/examples/
  robot-arm-demo/
    demo.mcfg
    demo.mec
  browser-robot-arm-demo/
    demo.js
    demo.mcfg
    demo.mec
```

2. What the guide demonstrates
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The robot arm host is a demo provider. It is useful for documenting the host model because it has provider-specific operations rather than only generic `read` and `write`.

A Mech program can bind a robot context and send commands to it. The host receives the command, records mock state, and exposes readable state paths.

3. Provider reference
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For the provider contract, see [Robot Arm Host](/hosts/robot-arm/docs/index.html).
